_decoded_content.name: Slide on Phone Mount for Permobil Wheelchair Joystick
_decoded_content.description:
Phone mount that slides over the joystick of the wheelchair, allowing for a quick setup. Permobil uses two different joystick modules (PJSM and CJSM2).  The main difference is the CJSM2 version has 2 extra buttons and larger screen compared to the PJSM. One of the pictures shows the difference. 

PJSM 3 Versions (CJSM2 does not currently have a "fixed" version) 

1) Fixed Position (* Please note this may increase your w/c width turning tight turns, i.e. door ways)  

2) Side Mounted - (Right or Left)

3) Height and Angle Adjustable (Picture shows one link of loc-line, but additional loc-line can be used for desired height) - 
                 Parts required: 
                 - (1) 3/4" Double Socket (61514 orange 4 pack), black available in larger 
                 quantities
                 -(1) 3/4" Elbow (61515 orange 2 pack), black available in larger quantities
                 -(2) 3/4" Fixed Mount (60533 orange 2 pack), black available in larger quantities
             **Optional 3D part that prevents phone clamp from Spinning**

Print Settings:
Printed on Bambu Lap X1C/P1S
Recommend PETG for extra strength - print as oriented
If using support - should only fill in the bottom indentations for the 3/4" fixed loc-line mount
Gyroid Infill pattern will provide the best appearance and better strength if using PETG
75-80% infill

Above settings work well with Bambu Lab X1C and P1S. Tolerances should be allow the phone mount to slip on/loff easily, but not too loose that it rattles. 

Parts Required:
1) Plastic Tripod Cell Phone Holder Adapter - One brand on Amazon is call "Vastar", but there are many similar generic versions - The anti spinner 3D printed adapter tested on this version specifically. Threadlocker can also be used instead. 
2) 1/4"x20 x 5/8" Screw Pan Head Phillips (**side mounted requires shorter 3/8" 1/4x20)

Tools - Phillips Screwdriver, Right angle Phillips Screwdriver will make it easier for the side mounted version (but not necessary)

Please note this is not a remix of another model. The slide on Joystick concept is not new. There are other similar styles of phone mounts that can be found online.
